The oracle bone script form consisted of two strings of five [[cowry|cowries]]. Some forms of the oracle bone script contained an additional {{zh-l|*人}} which later evolved into {{och-l|勹}}, which served as a phonetic component.

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' erroneously suggests {{och-l|朋}} was the ancient form of {{och-l|鳳}}.

